Foot and mouth disease, Mozambique
----------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 5 Jun 2015 from Dr Jose Libombo Jr, national director, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Maputo, Mozambique.

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 20 May 2015
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 27 May 2015
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: October 2014
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: pending
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks, total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Mapulanguene-Sede, Mapulanguene, Magude, Maputo
Date of start of the outbreak: 20 May 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 15 000 / 35 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: The disease affects cattle of all ages and both sexes and the main findings are mouth and foot lesions, excessive salivation and fever. The affected area is in the FMD control zone near Kruger National Park in South Africa and Limpopo National Park in Mozambique.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0.23 / 0.00 / 0.00/ 0.00
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: contact with wild species

Epidemiological comments: The current drought situation in the region is contributing to the concentration of high number of stock in a few water bodies and increasing the movement of susceptible animals and interactions with wildlife species.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; movement control inside the country; screening; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Central Veterinary Laboratory of the Agricultural Research Institute of Mozambique (IIAM) (National laboratory) / Cattle / non-structural protein ELISA / 27 May 2015 / Positive
Botswana Vaccine Institute (OIE's Reference Laboratory) / Cattle / serotyping / - / Pending
Botswana Vaccine Institute (OIE's Reference Laboratory) / Cattle / virus isolation / - / Pending
Botswana Vaccine Institute (OIE's Reference Laboratory) / Cattle / virus nautralisation test (VNT) / - / Pending

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In July 2014, Mozambique reported foot and mouth disease (FMD). For that event, 3 outbreaks associated with serotype SAT-2 were reported. In response to the outbreak, 101 371 cattle were vaccinated in the Maputo province using a trivalent SAT 1, 2 and 3 vaccine. According to Mozambique's last follow-up report on 26 Jan 2015, the event is still "continuing". See follow-up report No 3 at
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/temp/reports/en_fup_0000017061_20150126_165928.pdf.

A map of the administrative divisions of Mozambique is available at http://www.ephotopix.com/image/africa/mozambique_political_map.gif. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3414504,177.]
